<h2>Tree Select</h2>
<p>The hierarchical member of the <a href="/blocks/droplist/">droplist</a> family — selecting node(s) from
a nested tree. Per decision <a href="/backlog/064-tree-select-block/">#064</a> it is thin trait selection
over composed paradigms: it realizes the <a href="/intents/hierarchy/">hierarchy</a> intent and composes
<a href="/intents/selection/">selection</a> and <a href="/intents/disclosure/">disclosure</a> (per-node
expand state). <code>TreeSelectBehavior</code> is the reference runtime.</p>

<h3>What it provides</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Builds the tree from a declarative <code>TreeNode[]</code> (<code>{ id, label, children?,
    selectable? }</code>) into a <code>role="tree"</code> of <code>role="treeitem"</code> /
    <code>role="group"</code>.</li>
  <li>Node selection (<code>aria-checked</code>), <code>model: single | multiple</code>, optional
    <code>cascade</code> where toggling a parent toggles its descendants and a partially-checked parent
    reads <code>mixed</code>. Emits <code>tree-change</code>.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Web Standards Alignment</h3>
<we-data-table>
<table class="data-table">
  <tr><th>Standard</th><th>Status</th><th>How We Adopt It</th></tr>
  <tr>
    <td><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/treeview/">WAI-ARIA APG Tree View</a></td>
    <td>W3C WAI-ARIA APG</td>
    <td>Each node is a <code>role="treeitem"</code> with <code>aria-level</code> / <code>aria-setsize</code>
      / <code>aria-posinset</code>; child lists are <code>role="group"</code>; a parent carries
      <code>aria-expanded</code>; the active node is the sole tabbable one (roving tabindex).</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Tree keyboard interaction</td>
    <td>APG</td>
    <td><kbd>Down</kbd>/<kbd>Up</kbd> move through visible nodes; <kbd>Right</kbd> expands then descends;
      <kbd>Left</kbd> collapses then ascends to the parent; <kbd>Home</kbd>/<kbd>End</kbd> jump;
      <kbd>Space</kbd>/<kbd>Enter</kbd> toggle selection or expansion.</td>
  </tr>
</table>
</we-data-table>

<h3>Native-first</h3>
<p>The accessible baseline degrades to a single-level grouped <code>&lt;select&gt;</code>; the tree adds
multi-level structure and expansion on top. Consumed directly: <code>new TreeSelectBehavior(host, nodes,
{ model, cascade })</code>.</p>
